Hey @collect-coder sorry for the delayed response. Sorry about the trouble, I'm not sure why that happened during the migration. If you want to get around running migrations you can load a contract from its address as follows:
```javascript
const MyContract = artifacts.require("MyContract");
const instance = MyContract.at("<addressOfDeployedContract>");
//... do stuff with instance
```

I don't know if this helps...sorry I can't give you more insight on the gas issues. During migrations it should give you some sort of report on gas usage etc.

And at first glance your config looks correct. You could perhaps try omitting the gas values? Truffle will calculate some sensible defaults according to conditions.
